race.comment: The local Matt Dunn yard may hold the aces. SPICY WINGS (3) did a good job last start beaten 0.6L at Ballina over 1015m. The longer sprint suits and he's sure to have taken fitness and learning. With average luck he can go one better. Stablemate INSTA WORTHY (4) has raced favourite all three runs this preparation and has fallen short. He should position closer today and the senior hoop is reunited. Deserves another chance. PENSIERO (8) made further improvement beaten less than a length at Beaudesert. Maps well and the city-trained galloper will get her chance. ARTIE LADY (10) also lines up for the Dunn yard. Looked a run short at Coffs Harbour after a switch from a Victorian stable. Has an awkward gate but the blinkers are applied for the first time and we're likely to see improvement.
